INSERT INTO TUMOR_MARKER (IDENTIFIER,CODE,DISPLAY_NAME,DESCRIPTION) VALUES(nextval('serial'),'Plasma CRP','Plasma C-Reactive Protein','Plasma is the fluid (noncellular) portion of the circulating blood, as distinguished from the serum that is the fluid portion of the blood obtained by removal of the fibrin clot and blood cells after coagulation.: C-reactive protein [precursor] (224 aa, ~25 kDa) is encoded by the CRP gene. This protein is cleaved during biological activation and is associated with host defense mechanisms and inflammatory responses.');
INSERT INTO TUMOR_MARKER (IDENTIFIER,CODE,DISPLAY_NAME,DESCRIPTION) VALUES(nextval('serial'),'Zileuton','Zileuton','A synthetic derivative of hydroxyurea with antiasthmatic properties. The leukotriene inhibitor zileuton blocks 5-lipoxygenase, which catalyzes the formation of leukotrienes from arachidonic acid; causes bronchodilation; decreases bronchial mucous secretion and edema; and may prevent or decrease the symptoms of asthma. (NCI04)');
INSERT INTO TUMOR_MARKER (IDENTIFIER,CODE,DISPLAY_NAME,DESCRIPTION) VALUES(nextval('serial'),'Urinary PGE-M','Urinary prostaglandin E metabolite','Encoded by human PTGS1 Gene (PGHS Family), alternative constitutive homodimeric monotopic ER membrane Prostaglandin-Endoperoxide Synthase 1 isoforms contain an EGF-like domain and identical N/C-regions: long (599-aa, 69-kD precursor) and short (562-aa). Additional glycosylated gene products with altered (uncleaved) signal peptide, COX3 and PCOX1A (lacking COX activity), reside in cell membranes. Rate-limiting in prostaglandin and thromboxane synthesis, bifunctional PTGS1 appears involved in cell signaling, angiogenesis, and tissue homeostasis. PGH COX activity converts arachidonate to PGG2; PGH peroxidase converts PGG2 to PGH2. COX1 is inhibited by NSAIDs such as aspirin (irreversible ser529 acetylation). (from LocusLink, Swiss-Prot, OMIM, and NCI): Having to do with urine or the organs of the body that produce and get rid of urine.: Any substance involved in metabolism, either as a product of metabolism or as necessary for metabolism. ');
INSERT INTO TUMOR_MARKER (IDENTIFIER,CODE,DISPLAY_NAME,DESCRIPTION) VALUES(nextval('serial'),'Urinary LTE4','Urinary Leukotriene E4','Having to do with urine or the organs of the body that produce and get rid of urine.: A family of biologically active compounds derived from arachidonic acid by oxidative metabolism through the 5-lipoxygenase pathway. They participate in host defense reactions and pathophysiological conditions such as immediate hypersensitivity and inflammation. They have potent actions on many essential organs and systems, including the cardiovascular, pulmonary, and central nervous system as well as the gastrointestinal tract and the immune system.');
